      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is no single, unified academic consensus on the relationship between race and IQ scores, as the field is deeply polarized between researchers interpreting historical data as evidence of innate racial differences and those viewing it as the result of systemic inequality and test bias. While mainstream developmental psychology largely rejects biological determinism in its critique of group gaps, sociologists desperately emphasize that observed differences are overwhelmingly driven by environmental factors like poverty, education quality, and stress rather than genetics. Leading experts currently agree that IQ testing is fundamentally a cultural assessment that requires rigorous contextual analysis before any racial disparities can be meaningfully interpreted.",
