    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, so if the hereditarian view is that these gaps are a statistically significant reality, how do they usually frame the implications of those findings? like, when looking at the data, do they tend to conclude that certain groups have a different 'natural' cognitive ceiling or potential compared to others?",
